<%- include('partials/head', { title: 'comparison' }) %>
<%- include('partials/nav') %>

<div class="page" id="main-content" role="main">
<section class="page-section">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="page-header a-fade-up">
      <div class="section-tag">comparison</div>
      <h2>perch. vs. the alternatives. there aren't many.</h2>
      <p>the honest truth: there's no other product that does exactly what perch. does. the closest options are either doing nothing or using a tool built for a completely different job. here's how they stack up.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="comp-table a-fade-up">
      <div class="comp-head">
        <div class="comp-c1"></div>
        <div class="comp-c2">doing nothing</div>
        <div class="comp-c3">budgeting apps</div>
        <div class="comp-c4 accent-col">perch.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="comp-row">
        <div class="comp-c1 comp-label">what it tracks</div>
        <div class="comp-c2">nothing — until the payment fails</div>
        <div class="comp-c3">past spending, categorised</div>
        <div class="comp-c4 accent-col">future renewals, with deadlines</div>
      </div>

      <div class="comp-row">
        <div class="comp-c1 comp-label">time horizon</div>
        <div class="comp-c2">backward (when money's already gone)</div>
        <div class="comp-c3">backward (what you already spent)</div>
        <div class="comp-c4 accent-col">forward (what's about to renew)</div>
      </div>

      <div class="comp-row">
        <div class="comp-c1 comp-label">setup time</div>
        <div class="comp-c2">zero — but you pay for it later</div>
        <div class="comp-c3">30–60 min linking accounts, categorising</div>
        <div class="comp-c4 accent-col">~2 min — forward an email, done</div>
      </div>

      <div class="comp-row">
        <div class="comp-c1 comp-label">bank or card linking</div>
        <div class="comp-c2">—</div>
        <div class="comp-c3 comp-bad">required</div>
        <div class="comp-c4 comp-good">never</div>
      </div>

      <div class="comp-row">
        <div class="comp-c1 comp-label">auto-cancels anything</div>
        <div class="comp-c2">—</div>
        <div class="comp-c3 comp-bad">no</div>
        <div class="comp-c4 comp-good">no — you always decide</div>
      </div>

      <div class="comp-row">
        <div class="comp-c1 comp-label">gives clear verdicts</div>
        <div class="comp-c2">—</div>
        <div class="comp-c3">raw data, no opinion</div>
        <div class="comp-c4 accent-col">renew, cancel, or renegotiate</div>
      </div>

      <div class="comp-row">
        <div class="comp-c1 comp-label">ongoing effort</div>
        <div class="comp-c2">none — you ignore it</div>
        <div class="comp-c3">log in and check regularly</div>
        <div class="comp-c4 accent-col">one email a week, 90 seconds</div>
      </div>

      <div class="comp-row">
        <div class="comp-c1 comp-label">notification style</div>
        <div class="comp-c2">the bank statement shock</div>
        <div class="comp-c3">push notifications, badges, alerts</div>
        <div class="comp-c4 accent-col">weekly digest — zero noise</div>
      </div>

      <div class="comp-row">
        <div class="comp-c1 comp-label">cost</div>
        <div class="comp-c2 comp-bad">£300–£1,000+/yr in overpayments</div>
        <div class="comp-c3">free–£14.99/mo</div>
        <div class="comp-c4 comp-good">£6.99/mo household, £14.99/mo business</div>
      </div>

      <div class="comp-row">
        <div class="comp-c1 comp-label">uk-specific</div>
        <div class="comp-c2">—</div>
        <div class="comp-c3">rarely — mostly us-first</div>
        <div class="comp-c4 accent-col">built for the uk market</div>
      </div>

      <div class="comp-row">
        <div class="comp-c1 comp-label">affiliate kickbacks</div>
        <div class="comp-c2">—</div>
        <div class="comp-c3 comp-bad">common — "best deals" = best for them</div>
        <div class="comp-c4 comp-good">none — unconflicted verdicts</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="page-section not-section">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="page-header a-fade-up">
      <div class="section-tag">why no direct competitor</div>
      <h2>because the problem isn't sexy enough for vc-funded fintech.</h2>
      <p>auto-renewal tracking doesn't scale to a billion-dollar outcome. you can't add a bnpl feature to it. you can't sell the data. you can't build a neobank around it. so the startups go after the bigger narrative — "your finances, all in one place" — and perch. goes after the specific job that actually needs doing.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="comp-verdict a-fade-up">
      <div class="comp-verdict-icon">→</div>
      <div>
        <h3>spreadsheets and calendar reminders come closest</h3>
        <p>and they work — if you have the discipline to set them up and maintain them. but that's the problem: you're doing maintenance on something that should be automatic. perch. removes the maintenance entirely. forward once, forget forever.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
</div>

